# Test: `ze interface help` lists the new operator subcommands.
#
# VALIDATES: offline CLI entry points up/down/mtu/mac/neighbors/routes/
#            clear/create-bridge are registered in the known-subcommand
#            gate AND surfaced in the usage table, so operators can
#            discover them via `ze interface help` or `ze interface`.
# PREVENTS: regressions where an offline subcommand is added but the
#           usage table is not updated, or the registration goes silent.

cmd=foreground:seq=1:exec=ze interface help
expect=exit:code=0
expect=stdout:contains=create bridge
expect=stdout:contains=up <name>
expect=stdout:contains=down <name>
expect=stdout:contains=mtu <name>
expect=stdout:contains=mac <name>
expect=stdout:contains=neighbors
expect=stdout:contains=routes
expect=stdout:contains=clear counters
